output.crosstab_text:
For first degree graduates of English studies, 1 years after graduation, Administrative and support service activities was the most common industry for and White ethnicity graduates, Professional, scientific and technical activities was the most common industry for and Black ethnicity graduates, Not known was the most common industry for and Asian ethnicity graduates, Accommodation and food service activities was the most common industry for and Mixed ethnicity graduates, Manufacturing was the most common industry for and Other ethnicity graduates, and Information and communication was the most common industry for and Not known ethnicity graduates.

The industry with the largest range in proportions was Information and communication where Not known ethnicity graduates had the highest proportion and Asian ethnicity graduates had the lowest proportion.The industry with the largest range in median earnings was Education where Mixed ethnicity graduates the highest median earnings (£27,300) and Black ethnicity graduates had the lowest median earnings (£23,500).The group with the highest median earnings was Mixed ethnicity graduates in the Education industry (median earnings of £27,300).
output.crosstab_title: Industry of graduate employment for graduates of English studies by ethnicity, one year after graduation, male and female first degree graduates from English HEIs, APs and FECs, 2018/19 tax year.
